commit.message: Fix typo
Support SVG Image
Added return types to docstrings, and fixed description of getDPI()'s return
Support paths as pathlib.Path (or anything convertible to str)

Remove dependency of unmaintained nose

The nose project has ceased development. The last commit is from Mar 3,
2016. From their docs page:

https://nose.readthedocs.io/

> Note to Users
>
> Nose has been in maintenance mode for the past several years and will
> likely cease without a new person/team to take over maintainership.
> New projects should consider using Nose2, py.test, or just plain
> unittest/unittest2.

Simplify tests by using the stdlib unittest. One fewer dependency.

commit.message:
Fix Python 3.7 Travis testing

Use 'dist: xenial' in Travis to simplify configuration. Allows using
Python version 3.7 without sudo declarations. Travis officially added
support for Xenial on 2018-11-08.

https://blog.travis-ci.com/2018-11-08-xenial-release
Fix spelling of word Endian
Make sure *.pyc files are not included in the tarball
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:shibukawa/imagesize_py
add TIFF support (experimental)

commit.message:
Pass python_requires argument to setuptools

Helps pip decide what version of the library to install.

https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/#python-requires

> If your project only runs on certain Python versions, setting the
> python_requires argument to the appropriate PEP 440 version specifier
> string will prevent pip from installing the project on other Python
> versions.

https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setuptools.html#new-and-changed-setup-keywords

> python_requires
>
> A string corresponding to a version specifier (as defined in PEP 440)
> for the Python version, used to specify the Requires-Python defined in
> PEP 345.
